cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a dynamic memory network to adapt the template to the target's appearance variations during tracking, which involves machine learning techniques such as LSTM networks and attention mechanisms. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of residual learning, which is a technique commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely.
